0.19.105-jcult0205 Beta

July 27, 2013 4:36pm GMT+8

Replacing !DOCTYPE or DTD. Because of W3C standards, i will not mention any html for doctype/DTD like this:

Original:
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">

Should Replace and must be like this:
<!DOCTYPE html>

Error fix #0003 : <a href="A*******"> mistake.

Solution : Some domains are case-sentitive in <a href=""> tags. I should rename it in no caps, (articles.html instead of Articles.html) and also the file is the same (if <a href="Articles.html"> it must be also the name in the file; Supposed File Name="Articles.html") otherwise it could be a 404 error even the target is existed.
